usage: lt-dc [...options...] [...files.xcpp...]

Flag Options:
[ --verbose ]                 be verbose, this is not the default
[ --warnings ]                have warnings, this is the default
[ --insert-namespace ]        look for & insert the per-directory namespace module, this is the default
The flag options can be inverted with a 'no-' prefix; e.g '--no-warnings'

Value Options:
[ -I<directory> ]             same as with any C++ compiler
[ --srcdir=<directory> ]      e.g. $(scold_srcdir)
[ --objdir=<directory> ]      e.g. $(scold_cxxdir), probably not $(scold_objdir)

C++ Files:
files.xcpp                    C++2a source code in the S.C.O.L.D. stylings that are so popular these days

